<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israelis Start to Mark Holocaust Memorial Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, May 1 (Xinhua) -- The public commemoration of
Holocaust Memorial Day began Monday night in the Warsaw Ghetto
Square at Yad Vashem Holocaust Memorial in Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
Israeli President Ezer Weizman and Prime Minister Ehud Barak,
among other officials and representatives, attended the hour-long
ceremony officially opening Holocaust Martyrs and Heroes
Remembrance Day and spoke on the occasion.
</P>
<P>
Yad Vashem Directorate Chairman Avner Shlev kindled the memorial
flame. Some survivors recalled the horrible memories of the
Holocaust.
</P>
<P>
As part of the commemoration observances, from sundown on Monday
till sunrise on Tuesday, businesses and "entertainment halls" are
closed down by law.
</P>
<P>
Sirens will sound throughout the country at 10 a.m. Tuesday
morning, traffic will come to a halt and people will stand for two
minutes in silent tribute to the memory of the Jews that perished
in Europe.
</P>
<P>
A series of ceremonies will be held on Tuesday to mark the day.
</P>
<P>
The Yad Vashem Holocaust Memorial in Jerusalem was established
in 1953 to commemorate the 6 million Jews killed at concentration
camps in Europe during World War II.
</P>
<P>
The Jew State has since been holding annual commemoration
ceremonies to remind people not to forget one of the darkest pages
in their history of suffering. 
</P>
</TEXT>
