<HEADLINE> Ecuadorians Demonstrate Against U.S. Presence at Manta </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, May 1 (Xinhua) -- A multiple contingent of Ecuadorian
demonstrators demanded Monday the departure of American forces
from Manta military base on the Pacific Ocean littoral.
</P>
<P>
The demonstrators shouted in unison anti-American slogans when
passing in front of the U.S. Embassy at Manta base and others
situated in the Amazons," said President of the Patriotic Front (
FP) Luis Villacis.
</P>
<P>
The FP leader said it was possible that American military
personnel placed for anti-drug combat would become an intervention
force in Colombia. 
</P>
