<HEADLINE> Wage Increase Welcomed in Nigeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, May 1 (Xinhua) -- Nigerian public, on general, welcomed
the government's raise of the country's minimum monthly wage from
3,500 naira (35 U.S. dollars) to 7,500 naira (75 dollars) Monday.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the increase, which Nigerian President Olusegun
Obasanjo announced at the Tafawa Balewa square in Lagos to mark
the International Labor Day, the president of the Nigerian Guild
of Editors Remi Oyo said the increase would no doubt encourage the
workers to improve their productivity.
</P>
