economy will continue to suffer, stressing we need to get Niagara
back on course.
</P>
<P>
She added: "I also hope that transporters and market men will
not raise fares and prices respectively that might cancel out the
good gesture.''
</P>
<P>
Paul Ejime, resident chief correspondent of the Pan African
News Agency in Lagos, said that the increase was a good beginning
for Nigerian workers who had for long borne "the brunt of
mismanagement that had characterized governance since
independence''.
</P>
<P>
"It is also an astute master stroke for president Obasanjo to
show up at the May Day celebration to, at least, defuse the
tension of fear of 'us and them' that had marked the relationship
between the government and the governed in the past''. 
