<HEADLINE> Iran Repatriates 7,700 Afghan Refugees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, May 1 (Xinhua) -- Iran has repatriated 7,700 Afghan
refugees in the past 20 days, the Islamic Republic News Agency
reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Within the framework of a tripartite accord reached by Iran, the
United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) and the
ruling Taliban government in Afghanistan, 7,700 Afghan refugees
have been repatriated, said Hassanali Ebrahimi, director general
for foreign nationals at the Interior Ministry.
</P>
<P>
He said 7,400 Afghans were voluntarily repatriated through the
UNHCR while 300 others left Iran on their own. Under the tripartite
accord whose details were not disclosed, about 3,000 Afghan
refugees will be voluntarily repatriated every week through the
UNHCR.
</P>
<P>
He said the Iranian government will put into practice measures
to prevent the repatriated Afghan refugees from re-entering into
the country.
</P>
<P>
He urged international organizations to allocate "a fair
assistance" to Iran to help cope with the refuge problems, taking
into account the presence of over 2 million foreign refugees in the
country.
</P>
<P>
Among the 2 million refugees, nearly 1.5 million are Afghans,
most of whom poured into Iran following the 1979 Islamic
revolution. Iran has always complained about the lack of
international help in hosting the refugees. 
</P>
</TEXT>
