Unions Federation, claimed that 2.5 million people took part in
rallies and processions organized by trade unions, which were
mainly raising economic rather than political demands.
</P>
<P>
The unions called for a new labor code that "would be agreed
with the trade unions and not the one that has been submitted by
the government," Shmakov said.
</P>
<P>
In Moscow, thousands of people, braving a sudden drop of
temperature, attended marches staged by leftist organizations and
trade unions.
</P>
<P>
President-elect Vladimir Putin is outside Moscow, vacationing
in the Black Sea resort of Sochi. He is scheduled to return to the
capital Friday. 
