<HEADLINE> Police, Protester Clash at London May Day Protest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 1 (Xinhua) -- Masked demonstrators at an anti-
capitalist protest in London Monday attacked a city fast food
restaurant.
</P>
<P>
At least nine policemen were hurt, including one was hit by a
flying brick and two others injured as a crowd smashed every
window in the McDonald's burger bar in Whitehall.
</P>
<P>
A neighboring souvenir shop also came under attack. So far, 28
people have been arrested.
</P>
<P>
Riot police have sealed off Parliament Square where thousands
of protesters had gathered to "reclaim urban spaces" by planting
seeds.
</P>
<P>
The day -- the end of four days of protest in the capital --
had started peacefully with an almost carnival-like atmosphere.
</P>
<P>
There was a massive police presence around Whitehall but little
sign of trouble early in the day.
</P>
<P>
Demonstrators dug up clumps of turf and planted seeds as part
of their guerrilla gardening campaign -- to return parts of urban
London to nature.
</P>
<P>
Protesters climbed trees and beat drums, spilling on to the
roads and forcing police to close the square where a statue of
Winston Churchill was defaced with graffiti.
</P>
<P>
Many of the protesters had dressed in colorful costumes. But a
smaller, more sinister number were wearing balaclava helmets and
masks.
</P>
<P>
Holiday leave for the capital's police officers was canceled to
avoid a repeat of last year's demonstration in the city's
financial center.
</P>
<P>
That protest by about 10,000 people started peacefully but
descended into chaos and injuries for both officers and
demonstrators.
</P>
<P>
Eight people were also arrested at a similar anti-capitalist
rally in Manchester. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
