<HEADLINE> Germany's Gotsch Wins First European Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, May 1 (Xinhua) -- Qianhong Gotsch of Germany took her
first major table tennis title by beating Romania's Mihaela Steff
in the European championships women's final in Bremen on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese-born Gotsch, 31, overcame a stomach virus and
needed five sets to defeat Steff 16-21, 22-20, 21-15, 13-21, 21-13.
</P>
<P>
Gotsch, a winner of the Europe Top-12 competition, had been in
fine form earlier on Monday when she beat another Chinese-born
German, Jie Schoepp, in the semifinals.
</P>
<P>
Steff, 21, the most improved player of the season, put up an
impressive fight against world number five Gotsch.
</P>
<P>
In February, Steff helped Romania take bronze at the world team
championships in Malaysia. 
</P>
