<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Telekom Rider Takes Henninger Tower Cycling Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, FRANKFURT, MAY 1 (Xinhua) -- Kai Hundertmarck of the
Telekom team overcame a wrong detour from the police that cost the
lead group a minute of its advantage to win the title of at Round
the Henninger Tower cycling race in Frankfurt on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Hundertmarck clocked five hours, 1:35 minutes to win the 206.1
kilometers race, edging Italy's Matteo tosatto of the Fassa
Bortolo team by 12 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Teammate Jens Heppner was third as the Telekom team won its
19th race of the year.
</P>
<P>
The top trio broke away and raced alone for 150 kilometers, but
20 kilometers before the finish police mistakenly sent them
through a narrow street with parked cars and cost a minute of its
three-minute advantage over the main pack. 
</P>
</TEXT>
