<HEADLINE> Performance Held for 6th Chinese Arts Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, May 1 (Xinhua) -- Actors staged a gala performance
this morning in Nanjing, capital of east China's Jiangsu Province,
as a taste of what's to come in the 6th Chinese Art Festival which
begins in the city on September 28.
</P>
<P>
Mainland dramatic groups will perform 50 plays at the autumn
festival, while actors from Hong Kong, Macao, Taiwan and elsewhere
in the world will stage ten plays at the state-level arts festival.
</P>
<P>
A favorite of Chinese people of all ethnic groups, the festival
has been held annually for 13 years in cities such as Beijing,
Kunming, Lanzhou and Chengdu.
</P>
<P>
An official from the festival's preparatory committee said the
core group of festival events will be held in Nanjing, while some
performances will also be staged in Suzhou, Wuxi, Changzhou and
Yangzhou, to give audiences the fullest view of the province's
scenery and customs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
