<HEADLINE> International Arts Festival Starts in Chinese Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 1 (Xinhua) -- A month-long international arts gala
was kicked off tonight in the Chinese capital with Bizet's opera "
Carmen."
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Premier Li Lanqing attended the opening ceremony
of the festival, themed "Beijing 2000", in the Century Theater.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,000 artists from 24 countries and regions will join
the largest series of performances ever held in China. The event
is jointly sponsored by the Ministry of Culture, the Beijing
municipal government, the State Administration of Radio, Film and
Television, and the National Tourism Administration.
</P>
<P>
Artistic groups scheduled for the festival include the Royal
Danish Ballet, Les Ballets de Monte Carlo, the NDR Symphony
Orchestra of Hamburg, Verenigte Buehnen Vien and the Israeli Youth
Symphony Orchestra.
</P>
<P>
A number of exhibitions will be held, focusing on modern
photography, Italian violins, and paintings from Yugoslavia. Other
programs will be staged on squares in downtown Beijing and on
college campuses. 
</P>
</TEXT>
