<HEADLINE> Weekly Highlights of Trade-Related News (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
-- China's largest agricultural production company signed a
contract with the U.S. Phoschem in Beijing Friday to buy 500,000
tons of phosphate fertilizer.
</P>
<P>
-- The PetroChina Company Limited (PetroChina) Tuesday signed
long-term deals with five famous computer companies from both at
home and abroad to purchase their computer products at
preferential prices.
</P>
<P>
The five computer companies are DELL, SGI, SUN and IBM from the
United States, and LEGEND from China.
</P>
<P>
-- The China National Offshore Oil Corp. (CNOOC) and Shell
Exploration (China) Limited Wednesday signed an oil contract to
explore a block in the South China Sea.
</P>
<P>
-- One of China's largest software suppliers, Shenyang Neu-
Alpine software co. Ltd and Finland-based Nokia have signed an
agreement Wednesday to establish a joint venture to develop
wireless data solutions and services for Chinese telecom operators.
</P>
<P>
-- Nokia signed its first contract with the Jilin Mobile
Communication Company (Jilin MCC) Wednesday offering a commercial
wireless application protocol (WAP) solution.
</P>
<P>
-- Whirlpool Corp., the world's leading manufacturer of home
appliances, is committed to expanding its business in China by
offering quality products and service. 
