<HEADLINE> Son Given 15-year Sentence for Killing Mother </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINHUA, Zhejiang, May 1 (Xinhua) -- A 17-year-old student who
killed his mother because he couldn't cope with pressure from
school was found guilty of homicide and sentenced to 15 years in
prison this morning in the first ruling on the case.
</P>
<P>
Court reports said that on January 17, Xu Li, a second-year
senior high school student from the Fourth Middle School in the
city of Jinhua, in east China's Zhejiang Province, was in a bitter
argument with his mother when he threw a hammer at her head,
killing her.
</P>
<P>
The shocking news reverberated throughout the country and re-
ignited controversies about China's current education system,
which puts enormous pressure on students to get high scores on
college entry tests. 
</P>
</TEXT>
