<HEADLINE> Three Gorges Area Adds More Scenic Spots </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YICHANG, May 1 (Xinhua) -- A dozen new scenic spots in the
Three Gorges Area have recently been opened to the public, in an
effort to add more interest to this already-popular sightseeing
destination.
</P>
<P>
In the first three months of this year, Yichang, a major city
in the Three Gorges Area, hosted more than 980,000 tourists from
both at home and abroad, a rise of nine percent over the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
Local officials attributed the area's tourist boom to the fact
that experts had been invited to help make new plans and promotion
campaigns for the tourism destinations in the Three Gorges Area,
and a number of onshore scenic spots along the Yangtze River have
been added.  
</P>
