<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indian Exports Up 11.58 Percent in 1999-2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, May 1 (Xinhua) -- India's exports stood at 37.537
billion U.S. dollars during the 1999-2000 fiscal year (April 1999-
March 2000), up 11.58 percent over the 33.64 billion dollars
recorded in the previous fiscal.
</P>
<P>
According to the Central Statistics Organization, in rupee
terms, the country's export growth was 14.93 percent in the 1999-
2000 fiscal as compared with the previous year.
</P>
<P>
However, the country's imports were estimated at 46.153 billion
dollars, 10.19 percent higher than the level of 41.886 billion
dollars in 1998-1999.
</P>
<P>
The trade deficit during the 1999-2000 fiscal was estimated at
8.6 billion dollars, higher than the deficit of 8.2 billion
dollars in the previous year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
