<HEADLINE> Rwandans Urged to Fight Corruption </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, May 1 (Xinhua) -- Rwandan Prime Minister Bernard
Makuzas Monday urged the country to fight corruption in all
sectors, Rwanda News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
"Corruption challenges sustainable development, Rwandans should
work in transparency and be accountable to the people they serve,"
the prime minister said on the International Labor Day.
</P>
