<HEADLINE> Viduka Named Scottish Player of Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 1 (Xinhua) -- Mark Viduka, the Celtic leading
scorer with 27 goals this season, has been named Scotland's Player
of the Year in Glasgow on Sunday by the Scottish Professional
Footballers Association.
</P>
<P>
After learned the awarding, the ex-Dinamo Zagreb player has
admitted he might not be at Celtic next season.
</P>
<P>
Viduka said: "I enjoy being at Celtic and the fans have been
terrific with me, but I honestly do not know what will happen in
the summer as there is a lot of talking to be done. I will wait
until after the end of the season to make a decision."
</P>
<P>
The Australian-born striker, who joined Celtic in December 1998,
initially took some time in settling, but has been in consistently
good form all this season.
</P>
<P>
Overseas clubs showed interests in Viduka included Inter Milan,
Deportivo Coruna and Monaco. 
</P>
