<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tea Website Opens in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, May 1 (Xinhua) -- China tea website was opened
recently in Hangzhou, the capital city of east China's Zhejiang
province.
</P>
<P>
The website www.chinateaguide.com, with both Chinese and
English versions, will provide cybersurfers with latest
information about tea market, on-line consultation and purchase,
art of tea-making, historical documents, magazines, scientific
achievements and distance training program.
</P>
<P>
It also has a large data bank and concise user-port
modification function, which will enable users to set up a small
data base of their own and modify it if necessary.
</P>
<P>
The website has long-term cooperation with China and overseas
research institutes, which will share the information and offer
technical support.
</P>
<P>
The website is jointly established by China National Tea Museum,
Hangzhou Noah Electron Ltd., Co., Tea Research Institute of
Chinese Academy Agricultural Sciences, and Zhejiang University.
</P>
</TEXT>
