<HEADLINE> Regular Flight Between Wuhan and Hong Kong Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, May 1 (Xinhua) -- The regular flight between Hong Kong
and Wuhan, the capital city of central China's Hubei Province,
made its first run here today.
</P>
<P>
With the approval of the General Administration of Civil
Aviation of China, the round-trip flight operates daily, according
to the Hubei branch of China Southern Airlines.
</P>
<P>
The former charter flight run by the branch for 13 years could
not keep up with the increasing demand, said a spokesman from the
branch.
</P>
<P>
The new flight will also greatly facilitate the transportation
of freight and mail service between the two cities, the spokesman
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
