<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Unicef Sponsors Class for Female Dropouts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, May 1 (Xinhua) -- A group of 15 female school dropouts
in northwest China's Gansu Province were recently enrolled in a
agriculture training course, a program partly-funded by the United
Nations Children's Fund (Unicef).
</P>
<P>
Also assisted by China Association for Science and Technology,
the program, the first of its kind in China, aims to foster a
contingent of able counselors who can spread information about
farming techniques among other female dropouts.
</P>
<P>
A senior official from Unicef's New York headquarters is now in
Lanzhou, and will assist with the training of the young girls, who
come from three poverty-stricken counties in the province.
</P>
<P>
Unicef sponsors similar classes in 16 other developing
countries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
