<HEADLINE> HK to Host International Seminar on E-Commerce </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 1 (Xinhua) -- An international seminar on e-
commerce is to open at the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition
Center on May 31.
</P>
<P>
Overseas speakers will share their experience and knowledge of
e-commerce with participants of the "E-commerce in the New
Millennium Seminar" for small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs).
</P>
<P>
Organized by the Information Technology Services Department (
ITSD) and the Asia Oceania Electronic Messaging Association of the
Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation, the seminar is aimed at
enhancing the awareness and knowledge of e-commerce among local
SMEs.
</P>
<P>
Apart from local speakers, representatives from renowned
organizations in Australia, Japan and the United States will bring
in their experience and knowledge of e-commerce from the global
and Asia-Pacific perspectives.
</P>
<P>
The seminar is one of a series of events organized by ITSD to
promote the adoption of e-commerce in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Major topics of this seminar include the definition and
implementation of e-commerce, the new business paradigm --
partnerships and communities, investment and payment over the
Internet, e-commerce enablement for small business and related
security and legal issues. 
</P>
