<HEADLINE> Pakistan to Revitalize Economy: Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, May 1 (Xinhua)-- Pakistani Finance Minister Shaukat
Aziz Monday said the overriding objective of the country's reform
agenda is to revitalize the economy for macro-economic
stabilization and poverty reduction on sustainable basis.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a one-day National Workshop on Poverty Reduction
Strategy here, Shaukat stated, "we want to maximize exportable
surpluses, make our exports internationally competitive and
thereby generate substantial employment opportunities and this we
believe is the only viable and sustainable strategy for macro-
economic stabilization that will lead to alleviating the level of
poverty."
</P>
<P>
Shaukat said that Poverty reduction strategy recognized that
the development of the country was synonymous with the development
of the people.
</P>
<P>
In poverty reduction strategy, sustained growth is critical to
mobilizing the resources. And without growth, "we would embark
upon a road that leads to the redistribution of poverty," he added.
</P>
