<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Export, Import Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, May 1 (Xinhua) -- The value of Indonesia's export in
March increased by 3.67 percent to 4.94 billion U.S.dollars from
the previous month when it stood at 4.765 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the import value also significantly rose to 2.245
billion dollars or 6.22 percent higher than the 2.114 billion
dollars in the previous month.
</P>
<P>
"Export value in March which almost touched 5 billion U.S.
dollars is the biggest in recent years. The rise was backed by an
increase in oil and gas export and non-oil and gas export as well,
" Chairman of the National Bureau of Statistics Sugito Suwito told
reporters here Monday.
</P>
<P>
"For the first three months of the year 2000, total export
value reached 14.099 billion U.S. dollars or increased by 38.7
percent compared with the same period last year when it was only
10.165 billion U.S. dollars. The export growth in the course of
the first three months of the year 2000 is 3.8 percent higher than
the last three months of 1999," he said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Suwito said, for the first three months of the
current year, import value also went up by 17.49 percent to 6.529
billion dollars compared with a year ago.
</P>
<P>
"The increase of the import value is supported by a rise of
import of oil and gas commodities which reached 565.1 million U.S.
dollars or 80.93 percent higher than the same period last year.
Meanwhile import of non-oil and gas commodities also increased by
8.37 percent or reached 406.8 million U.S. dollars," he added.
</P>
<P>
He said the increase in imports was dominated by capital goods
instead of consumer goods.
</P>
<P>
"This is a sign of our (economic) recovery," he said.
</P>
<P>
Suwito further said that if the political situation in the
country had been stable, the value of export and import would have
been much higher. 
</P>
</TEXT>
