<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Heat Wave Sweeps East Indian State </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
All the tubewells and wells in the town had gone dry as the
water table had fallen.
</P>
<P>
The thirsty town, being supplied water from nearby towns by
train since Saturday, has become the focus of the current summer's
misery in Orissa state.
</P>
<P>
The water received from nearby towns was being distributed in
different localities in tankers.
</P>
<P>
The town required 300,000 liters of water daily, but the
authorities could only provide 160,000 liters from available
sources.
</P>
<P>
According to official sources, the heat wave prevailing this
summer had till now claimed three lives in Orissa.
</P>
<P>
Local weather office said that the 47.6 degrees recorded at
Titlagarh for the last two days was the highest for April this
year though the town registered 48.1 degrees in the corresponding
month last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
