<HEADLINE> Number of Tourists Visiting Indonesia Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, May 1 (Xinhua) -- Despite political uncertainty in
Indonesia, number of foreign tourists visiting the country were
reportedly increased in March mounting to 341,008.
</P>
<P>
"Of the 13 entry points, number of foreign tourists visiting
Indonesia increased by 4.15 percent in March to 341,008 compared
to the previous month which reached 327,406 tourists," Chairman of
the National Bureau of Statistic (BPS) Sugito Suwito told
reporters here Monday.
</P>
<P>
He said during the first three months of this year, the number
of foreign tourists reached 962,400 or up by 1.98 percent compared
to the same period last year of 943,700.
</P>
<P>
The Indonesian government has targeted earnings of 5 billion U.
S.dollars from the 5.1 million foreign tourists who will arrive
this year, based on an average stay of 10 days, and spending of 98
dollars per day per tourist. 
</P>
