Sumatera), Palembang (South Sumatera), Bogor, Tangerang, Bekasi
and Bandung (West Java), Semarang and Solo (Central Java),
Surabaya (East Java), Bali, Makassar (South Sulawesi) and Palu (
Central Sulawesi).
</P>
<P>
Waving posters and banners, the demonstrators also made
orations rejecting the proposed oil price hike.
</P>
<P>
They also demanded the government observe May 1 as National
Labor Day.
</P>
<P>
According to the Antara News Agency, the International Labor
Day was also observed in Surabaya, Medan and other cities in the
country.
</P>
<P>
The commemoration of the International Labor Day was banned by
the New Order government led by former president Soeharto.
</P>
