<HEADLINE> Manila Eyes Asia, Europe as Job-friendly Markets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 1 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine government said Monday
that it is targeting Asia and Europe as job-friendly markets for
overseas Filipino workers (OFWs) while it continues to pursue
efforts to create enough employment opportunities at home.
</P>
<P>
Secretary Bienvenido Laguesma of the Department of Labor and
Employment said these markets have great potential for providing
good benefits for workers.
</P>
<P>
"This year, markets in Europe an Asia offer good potential for
our overseas workers," Laguesma said in a radio interview.
</P>
<P>
But he stressed that this remains a temporary measure while the
government is putting in place programs to generate enough job
opportunities in the country to encourage OFWs to return home and
stay here.
</P>
<P>
"If we are to look for opportunities for our OFWs, we would
focus on better-paying, skilled jobs for them," he said.
</P>
<P>
Philippine President Joseph Estrada has hailed OFWs as the
country's modern-day heroes, citing their contributions to
economic growth through their billions of dollars in remittances
annually.
</P>
<P>
Last year the Estrada administration intensified its efforts to
monitor conditions, and conclude several labor and manpower
agreements with countries hosting OFWs.
</P>
<P>
Protecting the welfare of OFWs is one of the three pillars of
the Estrada administration's foreign policy alongside promoting
economic diplomacy and enhancing national security. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
