<HEADLINE> Nigeria to Set up Anti-Malaria Clubs in Schools </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, May 1 (Xinhua) -- Nigerian President Olusegun Obasanjo
has approved the formation of Roll Back Malaria clubs in
post-primary and post- secondary schools nationwide, reported The
Guardian, a leading Nigerian newspaper, on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted the Presidency sources as saying that
Obasanjo has enjoined Education Minister Tunde Adeniran in concert
with the commissioners of education in the 36 states and Abuja to
work out strategies for floating the clubs.
</P>
<P>
The move is aimed at reducing the malaria scourge by half in
the next 10 years, as targeted by last week's Roll Back Malaria
summit held in Nigeria' s capital Abuja to create awareness at the
grassroots, the Presidency sources said.
</P>
<P>
At the closing ceremony of the Roll Back Malaria summit,
Obasanjo praised the students of the Federal Government Girls
College, Abuja for the formation of the first ever Roll Back
Malaria Club in the country, saying the initiative was worthy of
emulation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
