<HEADLINE> Foot-and-Mouth Disease Kills 50 Animals in Mongolia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, May 1 (Xinhua) -- The foot-and-mouth disease that
recently broke out in Dornogovi Province of Mongolia has so far
killed 49 husbandry animals in the country with nearly 4,000
infected, media reports said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Martial law has been enforced in the province as of Monday to
forbid any vehicles, people and animals from passing through the
area, the Montsame News Agency reported. 
</P>
