<HEADLINE> Paperhanging Experts Spread New Technique </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 1 (Xinhua) -- A new paperhanging technique has
become a focus of attention at an on-going symposium on mounting
skills which opened here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The new technique was invented by two experts on paperhanging
Zhang Yongxiang and Li Linru, who use very simple appliances and
substitute a new binding material for the traditional paste.
</P>
<P>
The paperhanger couple have so far trained more than 800
students and are trying to spread the technique both at home and
abroad.
</P>
<P>
The four-day event will also feature presentations by other
paperhanging experts, exchange activities in relation to
paperhanging and restoration of ancient paintings and works of
calligraphy, and the exhibition of a 2,016 meter-scroll marking
the return of Macao to China. 
</P>
