<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 1 (Xinhua) -- Thousands of residents queued in
front of bank counters to buy new treasury bonds today as China
began to issue 60 billion yuan-worth of treasury bonds.
</P>
<P>
This is the second batch of certificate treasury bonds issued
this year.
</P>
<P>
The issuance includes 12 billion yuan worth of two-year bonds
with annual interest rate at 2.55 percent, 30 billion yuan-worth
of three-year bonds with annual interest rate at 2.89 percent, and
five-year bonds amounting to 18 billion yuan with annual interest
rate at 3.14 percent.
</P>
