<HEADLINE> Cargo Plane Crashes Into Lake Victoria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, May 1 (Xinhua) -- A cargo plane with seven crew on
board crashed into Lake Victoria after overshooting the runway at
Entebbe International Airport in Uganda Sunday morning, the New
Vision daily reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The seven-man crew has been rescued by the Civil Aviation
Authority marine department of the Crash fire and Rescue Services,
said Works Housing and Communications Minister John Nasasira, who
visited the scene on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The crewmen, who were rescued in a record seven minutes, had no
serious injuries and were taken to Entebbe Hospital for further
observation.
</P>
<P>
Nasasira has appointed a five-man investigative team to find
out the cause of the crash.
</P>
<P>
"The investigation begins immediately. There is no time-frame.
It depends on the extent to investigations," the minister said.
</P>
<P>
He said the U.S. Federal Aviation Administration was expected
to help in investigations after they were notified.
</P>
<P>
The plane, which is registered in the United Sates and belongs
to Dairo Air Services, overrun the runway and crashed through the
perimeter chain- link fence before plunging into Lake Victoria. It
was later swept by mid- morning water waves back to the lake
shore. 
</P>
</TEXT>
