<HEADLINE> Ningxia Constructs Muslim Park </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, May 1 (Xinhua) -- Construction of a Muslim park, the
largest of its kind in northwest China, has begun recently at
Zaoyuan Village in the city of Wuzhong in Ningxia Hui Autonomous
Region.
</P>
<P>
The Yellow River Muslim Park, approved by the Ningxia Regional
Planning Committee, covers an area of 233 hectares and will
feature Hui Muslim's customs, culture and natural resources of the
Yellow River to promote the local economy.
</P>
<P>
The project will cost 200 million yuan (24 million U.S. dollars)
and will be completed in five to eight years. The first phase of
the three-stage project will cost 12.51 million yuan (1.5 million
dollars).  
