<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 2,000-Year Old Relics Found in Northwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, May 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese archeologists have found
sixty-three historical relics from three tombs dating back to the
Western Han Dynasty (206 B.C.-24 A.D.), in Guyuan County in
Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The relics include one a pottery cooking pot and five lead tomb
sculptures, coins, bronze items, pottery utensils and silver
ornaments.
</P>
<P>
The tombs were unearthed at a construction site, said an
archaeologist. 
