West China E-commerce Portal (Ningxia).
</P>
<P>
Ningxia and Utah share very similar geographic, natural
conditions with lots of desertification areas. Nevertheless,
Ningxia's economy is less-developed in China whereas Utah's
economy has grown at annual rate of over 8 percent in the past
decade thanks to the rapid growth of IT industry, bio-engineering
and medical apparatuses and equipment.
</P>
<P>
In an effort to promote its development, Ningxia decided to set
up e-commerce postal to develop IT technology and Web economy in
cooperation with the corporations based in Utah like Compaq and
Oracle.
</P>
<P>
An autonomous government official in Ningxia said such
cooperative efforts will enable industrial enterprises in Ningxia
to be more open to the world through webs.
</P>
<P>
Noting that there are currently nearly 300 computer firms in
Ningxia and they can be conducive for the operation of e-commerce
portal, the official said that the construction of the portal is
expected to start early next month.  
