<DOCNO> XIE20000501.0168 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar Seizes Nearly 3 Tons of Drugs in Q1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, May 1 (Xinhua) -- The Myanmar authorities cracked a
total of 964 narcotic-drug-related cases in the first quarter of
2000, seizing 2,836.94 kilos of drugs and detained 1,342 drug
offenders, according to the latest figures published by the
country's Central Committee for Drug Abuse Control.
</P>
<P>
Of the drugs seized by army units, police and the customs,
opium accounted for 255.16 kilos, heroin 24.1 kilos and marijuana
285.08 kilos.
</P>
<P>
In 1999, the Myanmar authorities seized 1,447.55 kilos of opium,
272.94 kilos of heroin, 274.48 kilos of marijuana, 262,821.47
liters of precursor chemicals as well as 28.75 million tablets of
stimulant drugs, destroying 12 heroin refineries.
</P>
<P>
There are now 41,336 hectares of poppy cultivation in Myanmar
with 86,537 drug addicts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
