<HEADLINE> Australian Police Officers Shot by Gunman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, May 1 (Xinhua) -- Three police officers were shot by
a gunman early Monday morning in Brisbane, capital of Quensland
state, Australian Associated Press reported.
</P>
<P>
The gunman shot a female officer several times in the neck and
face before firing and wounding another officer, both on a police
vehicle.
</P>
<P>
Later, the gunman shot a third police officer who was called to
the scene.
</P>
<P>
The shootings occurred on Brisbane's northern suburb.
</P>
<P>
The police officers were taken to hospital and two of them were
in a serious condition. The third was believed to be recovering in
a satisfactory condition.
</P>
<P>
A police spokesman said an "emergent situation" had been
declared in the suburb and major roads running through the area
had been closed. Residents in the immediate area were urged to
remain in their homes with their doors locked. 
</P>
