<HEADLINE> Financial Index of Major Chinese Regions: Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 1 (Xinhua) -- The following is the financial
situation in Beijing, the Chinese capital, in the first quarter of
the year:
</P>
<P>
The outstanding amount of all deposits in Beijing was 824.82
billion yuan at the end of March, down by 2.21 billion yuan from
the beginning of the year. Of the volume, 276.7 billion yuan were
local residents' savings deposits, up by 8.63 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The outstanding amount of total loans in the city reached 504.
79 billion yuan, an increase of 21.94 billion yuan from the
beginning of the year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
