<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Economic Index of Major Chinese Regions: Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 1 (Xinhua) -- Editor's note: Beginning today,
Xinhua is going to send some dispatches on major economic
indicators of ten major Chinese regions on a quarterly and annual
basis. The ten regions include Guangdong, Jiangsu, Shandong,
Zhejiang, Henan, Liaoning, Shanghai, Beijing, Tianjin, and
Chongqing. These provinces and municipalities make up the bulk of
the Chinese economy.
</P>
<P>
The following is a general economic development in Beijing, the
Chinese capital, in the first quarter of the year:
</P>
<P>
Beijing's gross domestic product (GDP) was 44.91 billion yuan
in the quarter, representing a growth of 10 percent over the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
The municipality achieved 1.35 billion yuan added value in
agriculture, up four percent. It also registered 11.1 percent and
9.3 percent increases in its second and tertiary industries with
added value reaching 17.23 billion yuan and 26.34 billion yuan,
respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
