<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0030 GMT, May 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON -- The British Foreign Office said Sunday that Foreign
Secretary Robin Cook has postponed a trip to Iran until July.
</P>
<P>
Cook had spoken to his Iranian counterpart, Kamal Kharrazi,
Saturday and new dates were agreed on, the Foreign Office said. (
Britain-Iran)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli Minister of Regional Cooperation Shimon
Peres said here on Sunday that resolutions on the problems of
Palestinian refugees must be put off until the withdrawal from
south Lebanon, the Israel Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the security cabinet, Peres explained that Syria is
trying to encourage the refugees against Israel.  (Israel-
Palestinian-Refugees)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- The British government is to build a 25 million pound
spy center to monitor criminal gangs through their use of the
Internet.
</P>
<P>
The Government Technical Assistance Center (GTAC) is likely to
be used to unscramble coded Internet messages, tap phones and
intercept e-mails. (Britain-Spy)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- British Foreign Secretary Robin Cook Sunday canceled
a planned trip to the Middle East to concentrate on the crisis in
Zimbabwe, the Foreign Office said.
</P>
<P>
His scheduled trip to Iran from 8-9 May has been postponed to
early July.
</P>
<P>
"It's because Robin Cook is very occupied with Zimbabwe. It's a
major item on his daily agenda," a Foreign Office spokesman said.
(Britain-Zimbabwe)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LAGOS -- Most of Nigerians are satisfied with the performance
of President Olusegun Obasanjo's government, the News Agency of
Nigeria reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The survey, named as "Attitudes Toward Democracy and Markets in
Nigeria", was conducted in Nigeria between January and February by
the U.S.-based International Foundation for Election Systems and
Management Systems International. (Nigeria-Obasanjo-Governance)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
AMMAN -- Jordanian King Abdullah Bin Hussein on Sunday held
talks here with Tomur Dawamat, vice-chairman of the Standing
Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC) of China, who is
attending the 103rd conference of the Inter-Parliamentary Union (
IPU).
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, the monarch thanked China for sending the
NPC delegation to attend the six-day conference and recalled his
visit to China last year, his first tour of Beijing since he
acceded to the throne in February 1999. (Jordan-King-China)
</P>
</TEXT>
