<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wimbledon Plunged into Relegation Trouble  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Wimbledon was plunged into
relegation trouble after they lost to Bradford City 3-0 at the
English premier league on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Bradford's win over a side reduced to 10 men for most of the
second half lifted them over Wimbledon, out of the bottom three
and into 17th place on 33 points with two matches remaining.
</P>
<P>
Wimbledon, famous in the past for the "Crazy Gang" combative
spirit that has kept them in the top flight since they first
arrived in 1986, sank into the relegation zone with 32 points and
two matches remaining.
</P>
<P>
Leeds United also beat Sheffield Wednesday 3-0 at Hillsborough
in a game that left Wednesday, who have a game in hand, last but
one and six points adrift of Bradford.
</P>
<P>
Leeds moved back to fourth place, two points ahead of Chelsea,
and still in with a chance of a Champions League slot. They have
64 points and are two adrift of second-placed Arsenal, who have a
game in hand, and Liverpool on 66 each. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
