<DOCNO> XIE20000501.0217 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Zealand to Host 2003 Triathlon World Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, May 1 (Xinhua) -- New Zealand has been awarded the
2003 world championships by the International Triathlon Union.
</P>
<P>
New Zealand Press Association (NZPA) Monday reported that the
decision in favor of Queenstown, a scenic city on New Zealand's
South Island, over closest rival London to host the event was made
Sunday night in a union congress in Sydney, Australia.
</P>
<P>
This year's triathlon world championships is being held in
Perth, Australia. Next year's world championships will be in
Edmonton, Canada, while Cancun, Mexico, was named as host for 2002
by the International Triathlon Union in its congress, NZPA
reported. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000501.0218 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Leverkusen Take Over Lead in Bundesliga </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Leverkusen took over the lead
after beating Hamburg 2-0 in the 32nd round match of the the
Bundesliga.
</P>
<P>
The game between the two teams was not so fierce as expected.
Leverkusen scored twice through Brazilian midfielder Ze Roberto in
the 19th minute and captain Jens Nowotny in the 30th minute.
</P>
<P>
After taking the 2-0 lead, Leverkusen controlled everything on
the field and kept the leading till the end of the game.
</P>
<P>
The win put Leverkusen back to the top of the league with 70
points, three more than BAyern Munich. They have a very good
chance to clinch the title as their rivals in the last two rounds
are not so strong -- Eintracht Frankfurt and SpVgg Unterhaching.
</P>
<P>
In the other match played on Sunday, Unterhaching defeated
Werder Bremen 1-0 through Andre Breitenreiter's goal in the 74th
minute. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
