<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2020 GMT, Monday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israel's first spaceman is scheduled to fly into
outer space within the United States' shuttle Columbia by mid 2001,
Israel's Air Force Magazine revealed on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Israeli Colonel Ilan Ramon was chose by American's National
Aeronautics and Space Administration (NASA) as a crew on the 107th
flight of the shuttle, which is due to take off next April or May,
according to the report. (Israel-Astronaut)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak is unlikely to
submit his plan of handing over three villages on the outskirts of
Jerusalem to the Palestinians for cabinet approval this week.
</P>
<P>
The plan, in which Abu Dis, Azariya, and Swahara would be handed
over to full Palestinian control in the next few weeks as a
confidence building measure for the two sides to reach a final-
status framework agreement, was originally expected to be discussed
in Wednesday's cabinet meeting, according to Israel Radio.
(Israel-Palestinian-Arab Villages)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
GAZA -- Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat on Monday condemned
Israeli government's approval of publishing new settlement
expansion tender in the West Bank.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a joint conference with visiting Australian Prime
Minister John Howard in the Palestinian self-rule city of Gaza,
Arafat said the tender for settlements expansion was negative and
destructive to the Israeli-Palestinian peace track.
</P>
<P>
It was the first public reaction from Arafat to last Thursday's
decision of Israel's Construction and Housing Ministry to issue a
tender for building 174 new housing units in Ma'aleh Adumim, a
mammoth Jewish settlement near Jerusalem. (Palestine-Australia-
Meeting)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- None of the presidential candidates won 367 votes, or
a two-third majority in the 550-seat parliament, to be elected the
next Turkish president in the second round of ballot in the
parliament on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Ahmet Necdet Sezer, the presiding judge of the Constitutional
Court who is the single candidate of the five parties represented
in the legislature, scored the highest number of votes with 314, up
from 281 in the first round last Thursday. (Turkey-Presidential
Race)
</P>
<P>
