<P>
TEHRAN -- At least six people were wounded in a mortar attack
Monday evening near an Iranian military headquarters in northern
Tehran, the state television reported.
</P>
<P>
The television said that a number of mortars hit at least five
spots in a sports complex in the Ararat Street around 20:15 hours
local times (1545 GMT) and one of the injured is in critical
conditions.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that Iran's main military opposition Mujaheddin
Khalq Organization (MKO) has claimed responsibility for the attack.
(Iran-Explosions)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Hamid Tefilin, one of the 13 Iranian Jews arrested on
espionage charges, confessed on Monday night to having spied for
Israel, state television reported.
</P>
<P>
"I am guilty. I accept the charges against me. I spied for
Israel," Tefilin said in an interview with the television after the
second session of the closed-door trial on the Iranian accused of
spying for Iran's arch foes, the United States and Israel.
</P>
<P>
Tefilin is the main suspect of the group of Jews. Earlier
reports said that four of the suspects had already confessed to
their crimes at the first court hearing. (Iran-Jew-Confession)
</P>
