<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, May 1 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. team upset hosts Russia 3-0
Monday night in the World Ice Hockey Championships in St.
Petersburg, dashing many Russian fans' hope to reverse a no-medal
history in the past six championships.
</P>
<P>
The new Ice Palace, packed with 12,350 spectators, witnessed
the Russian defeat in home turf despite a powerful roster that
included this season's NHL goal-scoring leader Pavel Bure.
</P>
